  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/1002",
  "title": "Include geo filtering in currentRefinedValues",
  "body": "I think it would make sense that the currentRefinedValues widget shows when a geo feature is used, either area filtering or search around a point.\n\nI'm not sure how this should be done though, as displaying lat/lng coordinates does not make sense.\nA quick hack is to provide a function for the template option and have an external source for the label to display depending on the coordinates/area filtering that is used.\n\nSomething like this:\n\n``` js\ninstantsearch.widgets.currentRefinedValues({\n                        container: '#active-filters',\n                        clearAll: false,\n                        attributes: [\n                            {\n                                name: '_geoloc',\n                                label: 'Location',\n                                template: function(a) {\n                                    return SomeObject.currentLocation;\n                                }\n                            }\n                        ]\n                       })\n```\n\nThoughts?\n",
